                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to Chargé
                            <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Boot directs the embassy to inquire if Japanese Government would acquiesce
                    in the American representative at Seoul being styled agent and consul-general,
                    thus following a usual precedent in the case of protected countries and
                    facilitating business relations with the Japanese resident.)</p>
            </div>
